While on his way to that monastery he does the observanceday procedure outside On the following day he enters and prepares the dwelling sets out water for drinking and water for washing and sweeps the precincts
Seven days before the invitation procedure he leaves because of business
Whether he returns to that monastery or not the first rains residence does count for that monk And there is no offense for the assenting
